INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (402501, 'The basis of optimism is sheer terror.', 40, 0), (402502, 'No evil is without its compensation ... it is not the loss itself  but the estimate of the loss  that troubles us.', 62237, 0), (402503, 'Let me embrace thee  sour adversity  for wise men say it is the wisest course.', 13, 0), (402504, 'Give thanks for sorrow that teaches you pity  for pain that teaches you courage-and give exceeding thanks for the mystery which remains a mystery still-the veil that hides you from the infinite  which makes it possible for you to believe in what you cannot see.', 8199, 0), (402505, 'A Christian could even give thanks for Hell  because Hell was a threat and a warning to keep him in the right way.', 33, 0), (402506, 'To every disadvantage there is a corresponding advantage.', 3433, 0), (402507, 'Too many people miss the silver lining because they''re expecting gold.', 63776, 0), (402508, 'If you count all your assets  you always show a profit.', 50567, 0), (402509, 'Too happy would you be  did ye but know your own advantages!', 1462, 0), (402510, 'Much unhappiness results from our inability to remember the nice things that happen to us.', 63777, 0), (402511, 'If we go down into ourselves  we find that we possess exactly what we desire.', 1662, 0), (402512, 'Be grateful for yourself... be thankful.', 2919, 0), (402513, 'Keep a grateful journal. Every night  list five things that you are grateful for. What it will begin to do is change your perspective of your day and your life.', 588, 0), (402514, 'There is no wealth but life.', 485, 0), (402515, 'Just to be is a blessing. Just to live is holy.', 63778, 0), (402516, 'Life may be hard  but it''s also wonderful.', 63779, 0), (402517, 'I like living. I have sometimes been wildly  despairingly  acutely miserable  racked with sorrow  but through it all I still know quite certainly that just to be alive is a grand thing.', 94, 0), (402518, 'Be glad of life because it gives you the chance to love  and to work  and to play and to look up at the stars.', 672, 0), (402519, 'To be alive  to be able to see  to walk ... it''s all a miracle. I have adapted the technique of living life from miracle to miracle.', 2523, 0), (402520, 'This is another day! Are its eyes blurred With maudlin grief for any wasted past? A thousand thousand failures shall not daunt! Let dust clasp dust  death  death  I am alive!', 2692, 0), (402521, 'The mere sense of living is joy enough.', 91, 0), (402522, 'However mean your life is  meet it and live it  do not shun it and call it hard names. It is not so bad as you are. It looks poorest when you are richest. The fault-finder will find faults even in Paradise. Love your life.', 1049, 0), (402523, 'Life is the first gift  love is the second  and understanding the third.', 8930, 0), (402524, 'To have a full stomach and fixed income are no small things .', 4, 0), (402525, 'For one mother  joy is the quiet pleasure found in gently rubbing shampoo into her young child''s hair. For another woman it''s taking a long walk alone  while for yet another it''s reveling in a much-anticipated vacation.', 63780, 0), (402526, 'How can they say my life is not a success? Have I not for more than sixty years gotten enough to eat and escaped being eaten?', 1014, 0), (402527, 'Sunshine is delicious  rain is refreshing  wind braces us up  snow is exhilarating  there is really no such thing as bad weather  only different kinds of good weather.', 485, 0), (402528, 'Only a stomach that rarely feels hungry scorns common things.', 2542, 0), (402529, 'My gratitude for good writing is unbounded  I''m grateful for it the way I''m grateful for the ocean.', 457, 0), (402530, 'Is it so small a thing to have enjoyed the sun  to have lived light in the spring  to have loved  to have thought  to have done?', 460, 0), (402531, 'When something does not insist on being noticed  when we aren''t grabbed by the collar or struck on the skull by a presence or an event  we take for granted the very things that most deserve our gratitude.', 30964, 0), (402532, 'You say grace before meals. All right. But I say grace before the concert and the opera  and grace before the play and pantomime  and grace before I open a book  and grace before sketching  painting  swimming  fencing  boxing  walking  playing  dancing and grace before I dip the pen in the ink.', 263, 0), (402533, 'Thank God for dirty dishes  they have a tale to tell. While other folks go hungry  we''re eating pretty well. With home  and health  and happiness  we shouldn''t want to fuss  For by this stack of evidence  God''s very good to us.', 33, 0), (402534, 'It is strange what a contempt men have for the joys that are offered them freely.', 3966, 0), (402535, 'Grateful for the blessing lent of simple tastes and mind content!', 24754, 0), (402536, 'An easy thing  O Power Divine  To thank thee for these gifts of Thine  For summer''s sunshine  winter''s snow  For hearts that kindle  thoughts that glow  But when shall I attain to this- To thank Thee for the things I miss?', 62370, 0), (402537, 'People call me an optimist  but I''m really an appreciator ... years ago  I was cured of a badly infected finger with antibiotics when once my doctor could have recommended only a hot water soak or  eventually  surgery.... When I was six years old and had scarlet fever  the first of the miracle drugs  sulfanilamide  saved my life. I''m grateful for computers and photocopiers ... I appreciate where we''ve come from.', 63781, 0), (402538, 'If only the people who worry about their liabilities would think about the riches they do possess  they would stop worrying. Would you sell both your eyes for a million dollars ... or your two legs ... or your hands ... or your hearing? Add up what you do have  and you''ll find that you won''t sell them for all the gold in the world. The best things in life are yours  if you can appreciate yourself.', 1005, 0), (402539, 'We can be thankful to a friend for a few acres or a little money  and yet for the freedom and command of the whole earth  and for the great benefits of our being  our life  health  and reason  we look upon ourselves as under no obligation.', 62237, 0), (402540, 'Health is ... a blessing that money cannot buy.', 62724, 0), (402541, 'Happiness lies  first of all  in health.', 63782, 0), (402542, 'A sound mind in a sound body is a short but full description of a happy state in this world.', 2375, 0), (402543, 'Health is the vital principle of bliss.', 63383, 0), (402544, 'If you can''t be thankful for what you receive  be thankful for what you escape.', 33, 0), (402545, 'Even though we can''t have all we want  we ought to be thankful we don''t get all we deserve.', 33, 0), (402546, 'Happy the man who can count his sufferings.', 782, 0), (402547, 'Happiness is composed of misfortunes avoided.', 26458, 0), (402548, 'Considering the fortune you might have lost  you''ll have to admit you''re rich already.', 63783, 0), (402549, 'I thank Thee first because I was never robbed before  second  because although they took my purse they did not take my life  third  because although they took my all  it was not much  and fourth because it was I who was robbed  and not I who robbed.', 4063, 0), (402550, 'Think of the ills from which you are exempt.', 8895, 0);
