INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403151, 'Friendship is a serious affection  the most sublime of all affections  because it is founded on principle  and cemented by time. The very reverse may be said of love. In a great degree  love and friendship cannot subsist in the same bosom  even when inspired by different objects they weaken or destroy each other  and for the same object can only be felt in succession. The vain fears and fond jealousies  the winds which fan the flame of love  when judiciously or artfully tempered  are both incompatible with the tender confidence and sincere respect of friendship.', 3905, 0), (403152, 'Accountability in friendship is the equivalent of love without strategy.', 6358, 0), (403153, 'Between men and women there is no friendship possible. There is passion  enmity  worship  love  but no friendship.', 40, 0), (403154, 'What men call friendship is no more than a partnership  a mutual care of interests  an exchange of favors - in a word  it is a sort of traffic  in which self-love ever proposes to be the gainer.', 154, 0), (403155, 'The more we love our friends  the less we flatter them  it is by excusing nothing that pure love shows itself.', 1695, 0), (403156, 'So long as we love we serve  so long as we are loved by others  I would almost say that we are indispensable  and no man is useless while he has a friend.', 449, 0), (403157, 'Friendship often ends in love  but love in friendship - never.', 432, 0), (403158, 'When we hurt each other we should write it down in the sand  so the winds of forgiveness can make it go away for good. When we help each other we should chisel it in stone  lest we never forget the love of a friend.', 63843, 0), (403159, 'Winning has always meant much to me  but winning ftiends has meant the most.', 63844, 0), (403160, 'Friends show their love - in times of trouble  not in happiness.', 542, 0), (403161, 'Life is to be fortified by many friendships. To love and to be loved is the greatest happiness of existence.', 9771, 0), (403162, 'Prosperity makes friends and adversity tries tliem.', 33, 0), (403163, 'A friend is one who dislikes the same people that you dislike.', 33, 0), (403164, 'A true friend is one soul in two bodies.', 1116, 0), (403165, 'Chance makes our parents  but choice makes our friends.', 24636, 0), (403166, 'The best way to keep your friends is to never owe them anything and never lend them anything.', 63845, 0), (403167, 'Forsake not an old friend  for the new is not comparable unto him. A new friend is as new wine: when it is old thou shalt drink it with pleasure.', 33, 0), (403168, 'The only way to have a friend is to be one.', 760, 0), (403169, 'Animals are such agreeable friends - they ask no questions  they pass no criticisms.', 215, 0), (403170, 'If you have a friend worth loving  Love him. Yes  and let him know That you love him  ere life''s evening Tinge his brow with sunset glow. Why should good words ne''er be said Of a friend till he is dead?', 63846, 0), (403171, 'I desire so to conduct the affairs of this administration that if at the end  when I come to lay down the reins of Ewer  I have lost every other friend on earth  I shall at st have one friend left  and that friend shall be down inside of me.', 1012, 0), (403172, 'Friends are like melons. Shall I tell you why? To find one good  you must a hundred try.', 63847, 0), (403173, 'A man that hath friends must show himself friendly  and there is a friend that sticketh closer than a brother.', 5587, 0), (403174, 'A friend in need is a friend indeed.', 41936, 0), (403175, 'There are three faithful friends: an old wife  an old dog  and ready money.', 1077, 0), (403176, 'I am wealthy in my friends.', 13, 0), (403177, 'A friend must not be injured  even in jest.', 62420, 0), (403178, 'Reprove your friends in secret  praise them openly.', 62420, 0), (403179, 'God same me from my friends  I can protect myself from my enemies.', 63848, 0), (403180, 'It''s the friends yo