INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403401, 'Nothing is ever lost by courtesy. It is the cheapest of pleasures  costs nothing  and conveys much. It pleases him who gives and receives and thus  like mercy  is twice blessed.', 63884, 0), (403402, 'Truth is a rough  honest  helter-skelter terrier  that none like to see brought into their drawing rooms.', 4093, 0), (403403, 'Friendship cannot live with ceremony  nor without civility.', 63885, 0), (403404, 'Don''t flatter yourself that friendship authorizes you to say disagreeable things to your intimates. The nearer you come into relation with a person  the more necessary do tact and courtesy become.', 24754, 0), (403405, 'Friends are like a pleasant park where you wish to go  while you may enjoy the flowers  you may not eat them.', 20175, 0), (403406, 'Friendship is honey  but don''t eat it all.', 63684, 0), (403407, 'Except in cases of necessity  which are rare  leave your friend to learn unpleasant things from his enemies  they are ready enough to tell him.', 24754, 0), (403408, 'It''s important to our friends to believe that we are unreservedly frank with them  and important to our friendship that we are not.', 1932, 0), (403409, 'Don''t tell your friends their social faults  they will cure the fault and never forgive you.', 1014, 0), (403410, 'There are worse words than cuss words  there are words that hurt.', 44106, 0), (403411, 'Nobody likes having salt rubbed into their wounds  even if it is the salt of the earth.', 7216, 0), (403412, 'Flattery makes friends  truth enemies.', 8413, 0), (403413, 'Before a secret is told  one can often feel the weight of it in the atmosphere.', 5094, 0), (403414, 'A cruel story runs on wheels  and every hand oils the wheels as they run.', 4093, 0), (403415, 'It is terrible to destroy a person''s picture of himself in the interests of truth or some other abstraction.', 217, 0), (403416, 'If we all told what we know of one another  there would not be four friends in the world', 144, 0), (403417, 'We all need somebody to talk to. It would be good if we talked ... not just pitter-patter  but real talk. We shouldn''t be so afraid  because most people really like this contact  that you show you are vulnerable makes them free to be vulnerable.', 63886, 0), (403418, 'If we were all given by magic the power to read each other''s thoughts  I suppose the first effect would be to dissolve all friendships.', 33, 0), (403419, 'The truth that is suppressed by friends is the readiest weapon of the enemy.', 449, 0), (403420, 'So often the truth is told with hate  and lies are told with love.', 138, 0), (403421, 'Give me the avowed  the erect and manly foe  Bold I can meet  perhaps may turn the blow  But of all plagues  good Heaven  thy wrath can send  Save  oh save me from the candid friend!', 62800, 0), (403422, 'A good friend can tell you what is the matter with you in a minute. He may not seem such a good friend after telling.', 61734, 0), (403423, 'Do not remove a fly from your friend''s forehead with a hatchet.', 7652, 0), (403424, 'Friendship will not stand the strain of very much good advice for very long.', 44024, 0), (403425, 'There is not so good an understanding between any two  but the exposure by the one of a serious fault in the other will produce a misunderstanding in proportion to its heinousness.', 1049, 0), (403426, 'A friend should be a master at guessing and keeping still.', 11, 0), (403427, 'A cheerful friend is like a sunny day  which sheds its brightness on all around.', 1200, 0), (403428, 'The more we love our friends  the less we flatter them  it is by excusing nothing that pure love shows itself.', 1695, 0), (403429, 'It is the weak and confused who worship the pseudo-simplicities of brutal directness.', 2728, 0), (403430, 'What a wonderful thing it is to have a good friend. He identifies your innermost desires  and spares you the embarrassment of disclosing them to him yourself.', 2843, 0), (403431, 'I always felt that the great high privilege  relief and comfort of friendship was that one had to explain nothing.', 3172, 0), (403432, 'Nobody who is afraid of laughing  and heartily too  at his friend can be said to have a true and thorough love for him.', 63595, 0), (403433, 'Don''t believe your friends when they ask you to be honest with them. All they really want is to be maintained in the good opinion they have of themselves.', 532, 0), (403434, 'Only friends will tell you the truths you need to hear to make ... your life bearable.', 11923, 0), (403435, 'Keep the other person''s well-being in mind when you feel an attack of soul-purging truth coming on.', 1377, 0), (403436, 'If it''s very painful for you to criticize your friends-you''re safe in doing it. But if you take the slightest pleasure in it  that''s the time to hold your tongue.', 2806, 0), (403437, 'Flatterers look like friends  as wolves like dogs.', 47362, 0), (403438, 'Friendship may sometimes step a few paces in advance of truth.', 8764, 0), (403439, 'A friend is a person with whom I may be sincere. Before him  I may think aloud.', 760, 0), (403440, 'Oh  the comfort  the inexpressible comfort of feeling safe with a person  having neither to weigh thoughts nor measure words  but pouring them all out  just as they are  chaff and grain together  certain that a faithful hand will take and sift them  keep what is worth keeping  and with a breath of kindness blow the rest away.', 15444, 0), (403441, 'One''s friends are that part of the human race with which one can be human.', 2683, 0), (403442, 'I should like to tell you again of my bitter troubles so that mutually  by recounting our grief  we can lighten each other''s sorrow.', 63887, 0), (403443, 'There are only two people who can tell you the truth about yourself-an enemy who has lost his temper and a friend who loves you dearly.', 63363, 0), (403444, 'Since we are mortal  friendships are best kept to a moderate level  rather than sharing the very depths of our souls.', 63888, 0), (403445, 'Forget your woes when you see your friend.', 63889, 0), (403446, 'Those that lack friends to open themselves unto are cannibals of their own hearts.', 1035, 0), (403447, 'Laugh  and the world laughs with you  weep and you weep alone.', 541, 0), (403448, 'When good cheer is lacking  our friends will be packing.', 33, 0), (403449, 'We have no more right to put our discordant states of mind into the lives of those around us and rob them of their sunshine and brightness than we have to enter their houses and steal their silverware.', 63890, 0), (403450, '''Tis the privilege of friendship to talk nonsense  and have her nonsense respected.', 2182, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403451, 'There is no man that imparteth his joys to his friends  but he joyeth the more  and no man that imparteth his griefs to his friends  but he grieveth the less.', 1035, 0), (403452, 'I am treating you as my friend  asking you to share my present minuses in the hope I can ask you to share my future pluses.', 3172, 0), (403453, 'The most beautiful discovery true friends make is that they can grow separately without growing apart.', 63879, 0), (403454, 'Trouble is a sieve through which we sift our acquaintances. Those too big to pass through are our friends.', 15505, 0), (403455, 'I have come to esteem history as a component of friendships. In my case at least friendships are not igneous but sedimentary.', 63158, 0), (403456, 'No man can be happy without a friend  nor be sure of his friend till he is unhappy.', 1348, 0), (403457, 'Friendship makes prosperity more brilliant  and lightens adversity by dividing and sharing it.', 20928, 0), (403458, 'The friend of my adversity I shall always cherish most. I can better trust those who helped to relieve the gloom of my dark hours than those who are so ready to enjoy with me the sunshine of my prosperity.', 9689, 0), (403459, 'The growth of true friendship may be a lifelong affair.', 844, 0), (403460, 'Constant use had not worn ragged the fabric of their friendship.', 201, 0), (403461, 'Even where the affections are not strongly moved by any superior excellence  the companions of our childhood always possess a certain power over our minds which hardly any later friend can obtain.', 1161, 0), (403462, 'In prosperity our friends know us  in adversity we know our friends.', 63642, 0), (403463, '0 summer friendship  whose flat-tering leaves shadowed us in our prosperity  With the least gust  drop off in the autumn of adversity.', 51711, 0), (403464, '1 loathe a friend ... who takes his friend''s prosperity but will not voyage with him in his grief.', 542, 0), (403465, 'In prosperity friends do not leave you unless desired  whereas in adversity they stay away of their own accord.', 63891, 0), (403466, 'There''s no friend like someone who has known you since you were five.', 7258, 0), (403467, 'Lots of people want to ride with you in the limo  but what you want is someone who will take the bus with you when the limo breaks down.', 588, 0), (403468, 'I have lost friends  some by death ... others by sheer inability to cross the street.', 113, 0), (403469, 'Friendship was given by nature to be an assistant to virtue  not a companion in vice.', 20928, 0), (403470, 'We are fonder of visiting our friends in health than in sickness. We judge less favorably of their characters when any misfortune happens to them  and a lucky hit  either in business or reputation  improves even their personal appearance in our eyes.', 8948, 0), (403471, 'Women rely on friends. ... That''s where we draw sustenance and find safety. We can count on our women friends when we need a good laugh or a good cry.', 27392, 0), (403472, 'The shifts of fortune test the reliability of friends.', 20928, 0), (403473, 'Never befriend the oppressed unless you are prepared to take on the oppressor.', 2247, 0), (403474, 'Trouble shared is trouble halved.', 3165, 0), (403475, 'Real friendship is shown in times of trouble  prosperity is full of friends.', 542, 0), (403476, 'Instead of loving your enemies  treat your friends a little better.', 20175, 0), (403477, 'One enemy is too many  a hundred friends too few.', 33, 0), (403478, 'Faithful are the wounds of a friend  but the kisses of an enemy are deceitful.', 5587, 0), (403479, 'Friends come and go  enemies linger.', 33, 0), (403480, 'The proper office of a friend is to side with you when you are in the wrong. Nearly everybody will side with you when you are in the right.', 286, 0), (403481, 'It isn''t easy to be the person who sometimes has to try to preserve your happiness at the expense of your fun.', 63234, 0), (403482, 'I like a highland friend who will stand by me not only when I am in the right  but when I am a little in the wrong.', 50656, 0), (403483, 'I don''t care a damn for your loyal service when you think I am right  when I really want it most is when you think I am wrong.', 62955, 0), (403484, 'Nature has been for me  for as long as I remember  a source of solace  inspiration  adventure  and delight  a home  a teacher  a companion.', 21405, 0), (403485, 'However deep our devotion may be to parents or to children  it is our contemporaries alone with whom understanding is instinctive and entire.', 7182, 0), (403486, 'Writers seldom choose as friends those self-contained characters who are never in trouble  never unhappy or ill  never make mistakes  and always count their change when it is handed to them.', 9697, 0), (403487, 'Fortify yourself with a flock of friends! You can select them at random  write to one  dine with one  visit one  or take your problems to one. There is always at least one who will understand  inspire  and give you the lift you may need at the time.', 62529, 0), (403488, 'Many a person has held close  throughout their entire lives  two friends that always remained strange to one another  because one of them attracted by virtue of similarity  the other by difference.', 63892, 0), (403489, 'Nothing is more limiting than a closed circle of acquaintanceship where every avenue of conversation has been explored and social exchanges are fixed in a known routine.', 1565, 0), (403490, 'A man with few friends is only half-developed  there are whole sides of his nature which are locked up and have never been expressed. He cannot unlock them himself  he cannot even discover them  friends alone can stimulate him and open him.', 4976, 0), (403491, 'Friendship is mutual blackmail elevated to the level of love.', 28414, 0), (403492, 'Scratch a lover  and find a foe.', 201, 0), (403493, 'We need old friends to help us grow old and new friends to help us stay young.', 24198, 0), (403494, 'Friendship is almost always the union of a part of one mind with a part of another  people are friends in spots.', 2683, 0), (403495, 'It''s the folks that depend on us for this and for the other that we most do miss.', 21572, 0), (403496, 'Time''s passage through the memory is like molten glass that can be opaque or crystallize at any given moment at will: a thousand days are melted into one conversation  one glance  one hurt  and one hurt can be shattered and sprinkled over a thousand.', 185, 0), (403497, 'Kind words can be short and easy to speak  but their echoes are truly endless.', 70, 0), (403498, 'The wise man''s ... friendship is capable of going to extremes with many people  evoked as it is by many qualities.', 48445, 0), (403499, 'Now and then one sees a face which has kept its smile pure and undefiled. Such a smile transfigures  such a smile  if the artful but know it  is the greatest weapon a face can have.', 25904, 0), (403500, 'I cannot concentrate all my friendship on any single one of my friends because no one is complete enough in himself.', 23, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403501, 'We need two kinds of acquaintances  one to complain to  while we boast to the others. -Logan Pearsall Smith No one person can possibly combine all the elements supposed to make up what everyone means by friendship.', 41098, 0), (403502, 'Every organism requires an environment of friends  partly to shield it from violent changes  and partly to supply it with its wants.', 2606, 0), (403503, 'Without wearing any mask we are conscious of  we have a special face for each friend.', 24754, 0), (403504, 'An old friend never can be found  and nature has provided that he cannot easily be lost.', 2087, 0), (403505, 'Years and years of happiness only make us realize how lucky we are to have friends that have shared and made that happiness a reality.', 63893, 0), (403506, 'To those who know thee not  no words can paint! And those who know thee  know all words are faint!', 63430, 0), (403507, 'It is one of the blessings of old friends that you can afford to be stupid with them.', 760, 0), (403508, 'Old friends are the great blessing of one''s later years. ... They have a memory of the same events and have the same mode of thinking.', 1081, 0), (403509, 'As in the case of wines that improve with age  the oldest friendships ought to be the most delightful.', 20928, 0), (403510, 'There is a magic in the memory of a schoolboy friendship. It softens the heart  and even affects the nervous system of those who have no heart.', 1827, 0), (403511, 'It is great to have friends when one is young  but indeed it is still more so when you are getting old. When we are young  friends are  like everything else  a matter of course. In the old days we know what it means to have them.', 63669, 0), (403512, 'When you are young and without success  you have only a few friends. Then  later on  when you are rich and famous  you still have a few ... if you are lucky.', 981, 0), (403513, 'Old friends  we say  are best  when some sudden di