uage most readily in the country where it is spoken  you study mineralogy best among miners  and so with everything else.', 62224, 0), (403583, 'Tell me thy company  and I''ll tell thee what thou art.', 62284, 0), (403584, 'Who friendship with a knave hath made  is judged a partner in the trade.', 31023, 0), (403585, 'The lion is ashamed  it''s true  when he hunts with the fox.', 3244, 0), (403586, 'He that walketh with wise men shall be wise.', 5042, 0), (403587, 'Life is partly what we make it  and partly what it is made by the friends we choose.', 1264, 0), (403588, 'If you always live with those who are lame  you will yourself learn to limp.', 62593, 0), (403589, 'Keep good men company  and you shall be of their number.', 33, 0), (403590, 'A man becomes like those whose society he loves.', 62549, 0), (403591, 'A wise man associating with the vicious becomes an idiot  a dog traveling with good men becomes a rational being.', 42902, 0), (403592, 'It is better to weep with wise men than to laugh with fools.', 8413, 0), (403593, 'A wise man may look ridiculous in the company of fools.', 1348, 0), (403594, '111 company is like a dog  who dirts those most whom he loves best.', 995, 0), (403595, 'Satan''s friendship reaches to the prison door.', 57898, 0), (403596, 'Have no friends not equal to yourself.', 819, 0), (403597, 'Friendship is seldom lasting but between equals  or where the superiority on one side is reduced by some equivalent advantage on the other.', 2087, 0), (403598, 'Friendship neither finds nor makes equals.', 2904, 0), (403599, 'You cannot be friends upon any other terms than upon the terms of equality.', 1970, 0), (403600, 'A man is known by the company he keeps.', 33, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403601, 'Friendship is nothing else than an accord in all things  human and divine  conjoined with mutual goodwill and affection.', 20928, 0), (403602, 'Friendship is a union of spirits  a marriage of hearts  and the bond there of virtue.', 2087, 0), (403603, 'To associate with other like-minded people in small purposeful groups is for the great majority of men and women a source of profound psychological satisfaction.', 1032, 0), (403604, 'Shared joys make a friend  not shared sufferings.', 11, 0), (403605, 'Seek those who find your road agreeable  your personality and mind stimulating  your philosophy acceptable  and your experiences helpful. Let those who do not  seek their own kind.', 38322, 0), (403606, 'To like and dislike the same things  this is what makes a solid friendship.', 4812, 0), (403607, 'Friendship is only a reciprocal conciliation of interests.', 154, 0), (403608, 'Friendship needs a certain parallelism of life  a community of thought  a rivalry of aim.', 2796, 0), (403609, 'True friends ... face in the same direction  toward common projects  interests  goals.', 26, 0), (403610, 'That friendship may be at once fond and lasting  there must not only be equal virtue on each part  but virtue of the same kind  not only the same end must be proposed  but the same means must be approved by both.', 2087, 0), (403611, 'It is characteristic of spontaneous friendship to take on  without enquiry and almost at first sight  the unseen doings and unspoken sentiments of our friends  the part known gives us evidence enough that the unknown part cannot be much amiss.', 2683, 0), (403612, 'Men only become friends by community of pleasures.', 2087, 0), (403613, 'If we would build on a sure foundation in friendship  we must love friends for their sake rather than for our own.', 42, 0), (403614, 'The reward of friendship is itself. The man who hopes for anything else does not understand what true friendship is.', 63858, 0), (403615, 'That friendship will not continue to the end which is begun for an end.', 4935, 0), (403616, 'The friendships which last are those wherein each friend respects the other''s dignity to the point of not really wanting anything from him.', 9518, 0), (403617, 'My best friend is the man who in wishing me well wishes it for my sake.', 1116, 0), (403618, 'I have friends in overalls whose friendship I would not swap for the favor of the kings of the world.', 1673, 0), (403619, 'I have always differentiated between two types of friends  those who want proofs of friendship  and those who do not. One kind loves me for myself  and the others for themselves.', 16473, 0), (403620, 'Friendship  like credit  is highest where it is not used.', 4, 0), (403621, 'Friendship without self-interest is one of the rare and beautiful things of life.', 62523, 0), (403622, 'I have learned that to have a good friend is the purest of all God''s gifts  for it is a love that has no exchange of payment.', 52944, 0), (403623, 'If you press me to say why I loved him  I can say no more than because he was he  and I was I.', 663, 0), (403624, 'He who looks for advantage out of friendship strips it all of its nobility.', 62237, 0), (403625, 'Friendship is always a sweet responsibility  never an opportunity.', 81, 0), (403626, 'Friendship with oneself is all-important  because without it one cannot be friends with anyone else.', 141, 0), (403627, 'In a friend you find a second self.', 63900, 0), (403628, 'Of my friends  I am the only one I have left.', 21159, 0), (403629, 'I desire so to conduct the affairs of this administration that if at the end ... I have lost every other friend on earth  I shall at least have one friend left  and that friend shall be down inside of me.', 1012, 0), (403630, 'Be a friend to thyself  and others will be so too.', 1348, 0), (403631, 'Friendship is neither a formality nor a mode: it is rather a life.', 10420, 0), (403632, 'Friendship is one mind in two bodies.', 3003, 0), (403633, 'Friendship''s a noble name  ''tis love refined.', 63901, 0), (403634, 'A friend is  as it were  a second self.', 20928, 0), (403635, 'Friend: One who knows all about you and loves you just the same.', 4, 0), (403636, 'A friend is like a poem.', 36717, 0), (403637, 'A friend is a present you give to yourself.', 449, 0), (403638, 'A friend is someone you can do nothing with  and enjoy it.', 63902, 0), (403639, 'Friendship needs no words-it is solitude delivered from the anguish of loneliness.', 851, 0), (403640, 'A friend may well be reckoned the masterpiece of nature.', 760, 0), (403641, 'Two friends-two bodies with one soul inspired.', 395, 0), (403642, 'In poverty and other misfortunes of life  true friends are a sure refuge.', 1116, 0), (403643, 'Friendship is a single soul dwelling in two bodies.', 1116, 0), (403644, 'A faithful friend is the medicine of life.', 63896, 0), (403645, 'Friends are a second existence.', 1255, 0), (403646, 'A real friend helps us think our best thoughts  do our noblest deeds  be our finest selves.', 33, 0), (403647, 'Friendship is a furrow in the sand.', 63903, 0), (403648, 'Friendship is love without his wings!', 62558, 0), (403649, 'True friendship is self-love at second hand.', 8948, 0), (403650, 'The real friend is he or she who can share all our sorrow and double our joys.', 14130, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (403651, 'Friendship is a word the very sight of which in print makes the heart warm.', 5895, 0), (403652, 'Most men''s friendships are too inarticulate.', 1782, 0), (403653, 'My philosophy is: anyone or anything that gives you knowledge inspires you.', 63904, 0), (403654, 'The feeling of friendship is like that of being comfortably filled with roast beef.', 2087, 0), (403655, 'The easiest kind of relationship for me is with ten thousand people. The hardest is with one.', 7820, 0), (403656, 'It is easier to forgive an enemy than it is a friend.', 63767, 0), (403657, 'To act the part of a true friend requires more conscientious feeling than to fill with credit and complacency any other station or capacity in social life.', 24622, 0), (403658, 'Friendship is an art  and very few persons are born with a natural gift for it.', 4775, 0), (403659, 'Female friendships that work are relationships in which women help each other belong to themselves.', 15437, 0), (403660, 'The language of friendship is not words  but meanings.', 1049, 0), (403661, 'I can trust my friends. ... These people force me to examine myself  encourage me to grow.', 863, 0), (403662, 'We challenge one another to be funnier and smarter. ... It''s the way friends make love to one another.', 63905, 0), (403663, 'If I made it  it''s half because I was game enough to take a lot of punishment along the way and half because there were a lot of people who cared enough to help me.', 62515, 0), (403664, 'Iron sharpeneth iron  so a man sharp-eneth the countenance of his friend.', 5587, 0), (403665, 'A friend can tell you things you don''t want to tell yourself.', 15439, 0), (403666, 'I suppose there is one friend in the life of each of us who seems not a separate person  however dear and beloved  but an expansion  an interpretation  of one''s self.', 426, 0), (403667, 'Love demands infinitely less than friendship.', 6546, 0), (403668, 'Good company upon the road is the shortest cut.', 33, 0), (403669, 'The particular human chain we''re a part of is central to our individual identity.', 51497, 0), (403670, 'No person is your friend who demands your silence  or denies your right to grow.', 753, 0), (403671, 'The best preservative to keep the mind in health is the faithful admonition of a friend.', 1035, 0), (403672, 'What is thine is mine  and all mine is thine.', 62134, 0), (403673, 'Do not protect yourself by a fence  but rather by your friends.', 55628, 0), (403674, 'If our friends'' idealizations of us need the corrective of our own experience  it may be true also that our own sordid view of our lives needs the corrective of our friends'' idealizations.', 63906, 0), (403675, 'In meeting again after a separation  acquaintances ask after our outward life  friends after our inner life.', 20540, 0), (403676, 'In real friendship the judgment  the genius  the prudence of each party become the common property of both.', 20818, 0), (403677, 'The thicker one gets with some people  the thinner they become.', 63907, 0), (403678, 'When our friends are alive  we see the good qualities they lack  dead  we remember only those they possessed.', 63787, 0), (403679, 'The company makes the feast.', 33, 0), (403680, 'When one friend washes another  both become clean.', 62291, 0), (403681, 'I observed once to Goethe ... that when a friend is with us we do not think the same of him as when he is away. He replied  "Yes! because the absent friend is yourself  and he exists only in your head  whereas the friend who is present has an individuality of his own  and moves according to laws of his own  which cannot always be in accordance with those which you form for yourself."', 1304, 0), (403682, 'In reality  we are still children. We want to find a playmate for our thoughts and feelings.', 63908, 0), (403683, 'Love me  please  I love you  I can bear to be your friend. So ask of me anything ... I am not a tentative person. Whatever I do  I give up my whole self to it.', 62356, 0), (403684, 'Most of our misfortunes are comments of our friends upon them.', 432, 0), (403685, 'Greater love hath no man than this  that a man lay down his life for his friends.', 5587, 0), (403686, 'Animals are such agreeable friends- they ask no questions  they pass no criticisms.', 215, 0), (403687, 'Great friendship is never without anxiety.', 63849, 0), (403688, 'One out of four people in this country is mentally imbalanced. Think of your three closest friends and if they seem okay  then you''re the one.', 3199, 0), (403689, 'She is one of my best friends. Why  I''ve known her ever since we were the same age.', 63909, 0), (403690, 'You never know how many friends you have until you rent a cottage at the beach.', 63910, 0), (403691, 'There are two kinds of people in the world: those who come into a room and say  "Here I am!" and those who come in and say  "Oh  there you are."', 33, 0), (403692, 'Friends are folks who excuse you when you have made a fool of yourself.', 33, 0), (403693, 'A word of advice  don''t give it.', 63911, 0), (403694, 'Advice is what we ask for when we already know the answer but wish we didn''t.', 405, 0), (403695, 'Here''s a toast to someone who''s truly a best friend - a person who goes around telling good things behind your back.', 62637, 0), (403696, 'My friend thought he was not gonna make it. Then he started thinking positive. Now he''s positive he''s not gonna make it.', 63912, 0), (403697, 'We cherish our friends not for their ability to amuse us but for ours to amuse them.', 399, 0), (403698, 'There ain''t no surer way to find out whether you like people or hate them than to travel with them.', 286, 0), (403699, 'It takes a long time to grow an old friend.', 15459, 0), (403700, 'With friends like you - who needs enemas.', 33, 0);
